#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.38:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Kaḷārakhattiyavagga"
msgstr "4. Kaḷāra the Aristocrat"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Cetanāsutta"
msgstr "38. Intention"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.38:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

#. VAR: ārammaṇametaṃ → āramaṇametaṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn12.38:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Yañca, bhikkhave, ceteti yañca pakappeti yañca anuseti, ārammaṇametaṃ hoti "
"viññāṇassa ṭhitiyā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, what you intend or plan, and what you have underlying "
"tendencies for become a support for the continuation of consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.38:1.3"
msgid "Ārammaṇe sati patiṭṭhā viññāṇassa hoti."
msgstr "When this support exists, consciousness becomes established."

msgctxt "sn12.38:1.4"
msgid "Tasmiṃ patiṭṭhite viññāṇe virūḷhe āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti hoti."
msgstr ""
"When consciousness is established and grows, there is rebirth into a new "
"state of existence in the future."

msgctxt "sn12.38:1.5"
msgid ""
"Āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbattiyā sati āyatiṃ jāti jarāmaraṇaṃ "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When there is rebirth into a new state of existence in the future, future "
"rebirth, old age, and death come to be, as do sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn12.38:1.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.38:2.1"
msgid ""
"No ce, bhikkhave, ceteti no ce pakappeti, atha ce anuseti, ārammaṇametaṃ "
"hoti viññāṇassa ṭhitiyā."
msgstr ""
"If you don’t intend or plan, but still have underlying tendencies, this "
"becomes a support for the continuation of consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.38:2.2"
msgid "Ārammaṇe sati patiṭṭhā viññāṇassa hoti."
msgstr "When this support exists, consciousness becomes established."

msgctxt "sn12.38:2.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ patiṭṭhite viññāṇe virūḷhe āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti hoti."
msgstr ""
"When consciousness is established and grows, there is rebirth into a new "
"state of existence in the future."

msgctxt "sn12.38:2.4"
msgid ""
"Āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbattiyā sati āyatiṃ jāti jarāmaraṇaṃ "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"When there is rebirth into a new state of existence in the future, future "
"rebirth, old age, and death come to be, as do sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn12.38:2.5"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.66"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.38:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, no ceva ceteti no ca pakappeti no ca anuseti, "
"ārammaṇametaṃ na hoti viññāṇassa ṭhitiyā."
msgstr ""
"If you don’t intend or plan or have underlying tendencies, this doesn’t "
"become a support for the continuation of consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.38:3.2"
msgid "Ārammaṇe asati patiṭṭhā viññāṇassa na hoti."
msgstr "With no support, consciousness is not established."

msgctxt "sn12.38:3.3"
msgid "Tadappatiṭṭhite viññāṇe avirūḷhe āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti na hoti."
msgstr ""
"When consciousness is not established and doesn’t grow, there’s no rebirth "
"into a new state of existence in the future."

msgctxt "sn12.38:3.4"
msgid ""
"Āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbattiyā asati āyatiṃ jāti jarāmaraṇaṃ "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"When there is no rebirth into a new state of existence in the future, future "
"rebirth, old age, and death cease, as do sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, "
"and distress."

msgctxt "sn12.38:3.5"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.38:3.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
